On Thu, 1 Nov 2012, Jamie wrote:

> over torquing the oil pan bolt for example,, will break the case, and that is 
> sort of a catastrophe..

yes this is kind of important, the oil drain plug is NOT the one in the 
center of the engine bottom, in fact you really shouldn't touch that bolt. 
the drain plug is several inches to the right (looking towards the front) 
and a larger bolt, all by itself not holding anything.

